<p><strong>The Radical Cross: A W. Tozer PDF</strong></p>
<p><strong>1. What is "The Radical Cross"?</strong></p>
<p>"The Radical Cross" is a classic Christian book written by A.W. Tozer. It explores the profound significance of the cross of Jesus Christ and its transformative power in the life of a believer. Tozer presents a compelling case for the centrality of the cross in the Christian faith, arguing that it is not merely a symbol of Jesus' death but a gateway to understanding God's grace, forgiveness, and redemption.</p>
<p><strong>2. Why is the cross considered "radical"?</strong></p>
<p>Tozer uses the term "radical" to describe the cross because it represents a complete reversal of human thinking and expectations. The cross challenges our natural inclination towards pride, self-reliance, and worldly pursuits. It demands radical humility, self-denial, and a willingness to surrender our lives to God. By embracing the radical message of the cross, we unlock the path to true spiritual transformation.</p>
<p><strong>3. How does the cross transform our lives?</strong></p>
<p>According to Tozer, the cross has the power to:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Free us from sin:</strong> The cross represents the sacrifice of Jesus on behalf of our sins. By faith in Christ, we receive forgiveness and are reconciled with God.</li>
<li><strong>Empower us with new life:</strong> The cross symbolizes the resurrection of Jesus, which offers us hope and the power to overcome sin and live a victorious life.</li>
<li><strong>Bring us into union with God:</strong> The cross breaks down the barriers between us and God, allowing us to experience deep intimacy and communion with our Creator.</li>
</ul>
